  sodium: 420 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and peel @carrots{3}; cut on an angle into ¼-inch-thick pieces. Zest ½ tsp zest from @orange{1}, then squeeze juice into a #small bowl{}. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic, 1 thyme sprig from @thyme{¼%ounce}, and all but 2 tsp minced shallot (save the 2 tsp for step 5). Cook, stirring, until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @jasmine rice{½%cup} and ¾ cups water. Bring to a boil, then cover with a #lid{}, lower heat, and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered off heat.

Meanwhile, place carrots, orange juice, @sugar{¼%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} in a #large pan{}. Cover with a lid and place over medium heat. Cook until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. (TIP: If pan dries out, add a splash of water.) Once done, stir in orange zest and 1 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon}. Season with salt and @pepper{}. Remove from heat and keep covered until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @pork chops{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in another large pan over medium-high heat (we used nonstick). Cook until browned on surface and desired doneness is reached, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate{}.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium heat. Add one thyme sprig and remaining shallot. Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}. Reduce by half, about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in ¼ cup water, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @cranberry jam{2%tablespoon}. Cook until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat. Stir in 1 TBSP butter. Season with salt and pepper. Add pork and any juices on plate to pan, flipping pork to coat in sauce.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}, then stir in 1 TBSP butter. Season with salt and pepper. Remove thyme sprigs from rice and sauce. Divide rice and carrots between plates. Arrange pork on top of rice and drizzle with any remaining sauce in pan.